Token.Abstract: A dispatcher that will use NSURLSession to send requests to the Piwik server.
Send a single tracking event to the Piwik server.

Parameter.Name: parameters
Parameter.Abstract: Event parameters. These parameters should be added to the path as a URL encoded query string

Parameter.Name: successBlock
Parameter.Abstract: Run the block if the dispatch to the Piwik server is successful.

Parameter.Name: failure
Parameter.Abstract: Run this block if the dispatch to the Piwik server fails. Provide a YES to indicate if the SDK should attempt to send any pending event or NO if pending events should be saved until next dispatch. E.g. there is no use trying to send pending events if there is no network connection.

Token.Abstract: Send a a bulk of tracking events to the Piwik server.

Parameter.Name: parameters
Parameter.Abstract: Event parameters. These parameters should be JSON encoded and added to the request body.

Parameter.Name: successBlock
Parameter.Abstract: Run the block if the dispatch to the Piwik server is successful.

Parameter.Name: failure
Parameter.Abstract: Run this block if the dispatch to the Piwik server fails. Provide a YES to indicate if the SDK should attempt to send any pending event or NO if pending events should be saved until next dispatch. E.g. there is no use trying to send pending events if there is no network connection.
